---
/**
 * context-engineering 0009 · Figure 3 — M2 "lost in the middle / U-shaped
 * attention curve" diagram.
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from
 * docs/context-engineering/lessons/0009-context-caching-ordering-and-security.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption incl. the footnote <sup>). It lives as an .astro
 * component, NOT inline in the MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with
 * raw inline SVG that uses kebab-case attributes. In an .astro file the SVG is
 * plain HTML, so it renders byte-for-byte.
 *
 * This figure references NO arrowhead markers (just axes, a path, and labels),
 * so it carries no <defs> block.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 600 240"
        role="img"
        aria-label="A U-shaped attention curve: strong at the start and end of the window, weak in the middle."
    >
        <text x="300" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >Attention across the window</text
        >
        <!-- axes -->
        <line x1="60" y1="170" x2="560" y2="170" stroke="#111110" stroke-width="1.2"></line>
        <line x1="60" y1="40" x2="60" y2="170" stroke="#111110" stroke-width="1.2"></line>
        <text x="40" y="50" text-anchor="end" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f">high</text>
        <text x="40" y="168" text-anchor="end" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f">low</text>
        <!-- U curve -->
        <path
            d="M70,52 C160,60 230,150 300,150 C370,150 440,60 550,52"
            fill="none"
            stroke="#b5179e"
            stroke-width="2.5"></path>
        <!-- zones -->
        <text x="95" y="195" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >START</text
        >
        <text x="95" y="208" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f">primacy</text>
        <text x="300" y="195" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >MIDDLE</text
        >
        <text x="300" y="208" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f">skimmed / lost</text
        >
        <text x="520" y="195" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >END</text
        >
        <text x="520" y="208" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f">recency</text>
        <!-- placement callouts -->
        <text x="95" y="40" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >instructions</text
        >
        <text x="520" y="40" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >the query + best doc</text
        >
        <text x="300" y="232" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-style="italic" fill="#9a2417"
            >Bury the key fact here and the model may never use it &mdash; even though it's "in
            context."</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        A callback to Lesson 1's "lost in the middle." Being <em>present</em> in the window is necessary,
        not sufficient — content at the edges is read; content in the deep middle gets skimmed.<sup
            ><a href="#s3" id="r3b">3</a></sup
        >
    </figcaption>
</figure>
